with the record company!

112
00:08:52.615 --> 00:08:54.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We haven’t signed it yet, though.

113
00:08:54.784 --> 00:08:57.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Like I said, what reason
do you have to hesitate?

114
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well… There are a number of things.

115
00:08:59.497 --> 00:09:01.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hachi!

116
00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:05.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry. Your cake was delicious.

117
00:09:07.046 --> 00:09:08.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Shin.</i>

118
00:09:09.715 --> 00:09:11.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Make me your wife.</i>

119
00:09:12.593 --> 00:09:14.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Shin! What are you doing?

120
00:09:16.055 --> 00:09:18.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Unable to play the guitar or piano,</i>

121
00:09:18.766 --> 00:09:21.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I could never become a member of BLAST…</i>

122
00:09:21.894 --> 00:09:27.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But no one can surpass the love</i>
<i>I feel for BLAST and their music.</i>

123
00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:32.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And I swear to this for as long as I live.</i>

124
00:09:38.911 --> 00:09:41.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In my opinion.
a straight-up punk band like us

125
00:09:42.081 --> 00:09:44.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
will do better in the long run
if we take our time

126
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:48.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and go around on our own for a while
building a fan base

127
00:09:48.379 --> 00:09:51.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
rather than suddenly going big
and signing with a record company.

128
00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:52.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why?
-Why?

129
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:58.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sure, there are many artists
as good as pros

130
00:09:58.389 --> 00:09:59.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who haven’t signed a contract
with a major label,

131
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but if you’re planning
on going pro eventually anyway,

132
00:10:01.892 --> 00:10:04.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
